sub_title: Recent (Res)MA Linguistics graduate at Leiden University with proofreading experience, specialising in children's non-fiction
summary:
I am a recent graduate from the (Res) MA Linguistics programme at Leiden University, where my thesis focused on classifiers in Arawakan languages. I am interested in descriptive linguistics, with a particular interest in the linguistic history of South America and linguistic typology. I am also a student assistant on the SAPPHIRE project.
I also work independently as a proofreader, with experience in children's non-fiction, adult fiction, academic work, and indexing.
